    a normal "Wow."
    j "Yeah, we've been spending a lot of time together lately."
    j "I like spoiling her..."
    j sigh "Although my pockets have been hurting lately."
    j "I don't suppose you could—"
    a "No."
    j "I didn't even ask—"
    a "I already know what you're going to ask for."
    j "But—"
    a "No chance."
    j "{i}Huff{/i}."
    j "You're so stingy for a friend."
    j "I mean I was only going to ask for a little!"
    a "Right."
    v "Maybe you would make more money if you stopped cheating on your wife."
    j serious "Who said that?"
    j normal "Anyway..."
    j positive "I really like her!"
    a "You said that about the last one, too..."
    j normal "..."
    j "So what's going on with you lately?"
    j "I mean, after..."
    narrator "You catch Valerie's eye behind him."
    "Even in death, her disapproval is palpable."
    a "It's been hard."
    a "But it's been going."
    a "Just focusing on the shop, the garden, you know."
    j "Oh gosh, the shop."
    j "You know, sometimes I wish I had stayed in the business."
    j "Desk job isn't for the weak."
    a "Yeah, I wish you had, too."
    j "I'm always here for you, though, even when I'm not...well, {i}here{/i}."
    a "I appreciate that."
    narrator "Despite his flaws, he does turn out to be a good friend occasionally."
    narrator "Rrrring!"
    j "Ah, I need to take a call."
    j positive "It's from her!"
    a "Ok buddy."
    narrator "Smiling like a kid, Jason checks into the next room."
    narrator "...leaving you alone with his bag."
    narrator "You wouldn't snoop around in a friend's stuff, would you?"
    a "..."

    play music "teatime.mp3"
    show valerie ghost with in_spiral
    v "Hmph."
    a "I know, I know."
    a "He really is a good friend, though!"
    v "Just because I'm dead doesn't mean I'm going to stay quiet about these scumbags..."
    a "..."
    a "Don't remind me."
    v "About what? Your scumbag friends?"
    a "No, about you being..."
    narrator "Valerie skips a beat and softens her eyes"
    v "Ah..."
    narrator "She brings a ghostly hand to your cheek, and you can almost feel it."
    v "Well, I'm here for now." 
    v "Let's enjoy it, shall we?"
    menu:
        "You're right.":
            narrator "She smiles."
            v "That's it, no need to be so down about things."
            v "We don't even know how long this thing will last, anyway."
            v "Might as well pretend it's as long as we want."
        "But it's not the same...":
            a "You know it's not the same."
            narrator "She looks away."
            a "I just can't stop thinking about it."
            v "I get it."
            v "I know it's not the same."
    narrator "Her eyes narrow."
    v "But there's another woman—one who {i}is{/i} still alive—who you can help."
    a "I'm not one to do confrontations—"
    v "You don't have to confront him."
    v "I'm just saying..."
    v "Doesn't she deserve to know?"
    v "You know what I'm saying, right?"
